{"build_type":"library","description":"The single writer of the trace ring (TRACE-REPLAY DEBUGGER). Pure RAM + CPU: atomic-fetch-add the cursor at the fixed trace base (0x610000000000), wrap by mask (keeps the TAIL on overflow), write a fixed 256-byte step record = {seq, full ucontext gregs block: GP regs + rip + eflags + cr2/fault-addr}. Lock-free; no Linux, no per-step doorbell (the decoder is woken once at fault-time, not per step) -> scales to millions of steps. Edit this package to change the trace record shape everywhere.","module_name":"append-trace-step-into-ring-buffer","package_name":"append-trace-step-into-ring-buffer","function_definitions":{"append-trace-step-into-ring-buffer":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"ucontext","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"tbase","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":106652627894272},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"mask","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16383},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"hdr","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":64},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"recsz","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":256},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"forty","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":40},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"atomic_fetch_add","address":"tbase","delta":"one","result_assignment_variable":"slot"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"i","